cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.CY, cs.DS, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the study of Internet censorship mechanisms used by major ISPs in India. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the analysis of network paths and requested domains, which falls under the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The study of censorship infrastructure and its coverage can be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society). The paper also involves the development of various techniques and heuristics, which can be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
